## GitHub Issues Integration

### Creating GitHub Issues (Optional)

**When starting work on an item:**

1. **Create GitHub Issue** (optional but recommended):
   - Title: Match TODO item
   - Description: Brief description
   - Labels: `priority-{1-5}`, `type:{feature|technical|infrastructure}`, `area:{feature}`, `status:not-started`, `effort:{small|medium|large}`

2. **Update TODO status**:
   - Change to üü° **In Progress**

3. **Update GitHub Issue status** (if issue exists):
   - Run: `./scripts/update-issue-status.sh <issue-number> in-progress`
   - Or manually update label: Remove `status:not-started`, add `status:in-progress`

### Updating Issue Labels During Workflow

**CRITICAL: Keep issue labels up to date as work progresses**

**When Starting Work**:
- Update issue: `status:not-started` ‚Üí `status:in-progress`
- Use: `./scripts/update-issue-status.sh <issue-number> in-progress`
- Or: Pre-work check can auto-detect and update (if branch name includes issue number)

**When Creating PR**:
- Update issue: `status:in-progress` ‚Üí `status:review`
- Use: `./scripts/update-issue-status.sh <issue-number> review`
- Or: GitHub Actions workflow can auto-update (if PR references issue)

**When PR Merged**:
- Update issue: `status:review` ‚Üí `status:completed`
- Use: `./scripts/update-issue-status.sh <issue-number> completed`
- Or: GitHub Actions workflow can auto-update (on PR merge)

**When Blocked**:
- Update issue: `status:in-progress` ‚Üí `status:blocked`
- Use: `./scripts/update-issue-status.sh <issue-number> blocked`

